From 6ec62d6cabe8280c1c2d3dde1644c4799bb7a5b9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Karthikeya <karthi@jovio.in>
Date: Sun, 28 Jun 2026 13:18:10 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(flutter): FCM push wiring + /forgot-password +
 device_tokens schema

- New services/fcm_service.dart: singleton handling
  * background message handler (top-level @pragma vm:entry-point)
  * foreground messages -> in-app snackbar with OPEN action
  * tap-to-route from background or cold start (msg.data.type ->
    /calls, /home, /billing)
  * APNs token wait on iOS before getToken
  * onTokenRefresh listener for token rotation
  * register / unregister with Supabase via device_tokens

- providers/auth_provider.dart: auth state stream now triggers
  FcmService register on sign-in and unregister on sign-out so
  pushes always target the currently-logged-in device.

- main.dart: replaced bare requestPermission() with FcmService.init,
  added global navigatorKey wired into GoRouter so the FCM service
  can route from background contexts. New /forgot-password route
  added to redirect allowlist.

- screens/auth/forgot_password_screen.dart (NEW): email input
  + Supabase resetPasswordForEmail. Generic success regardless of
  account existence (prevents enumeration); only rate-limit errors
  surfaced. Reset link points back to the dashboard's web reset page.

- screens/auth/login_screen.dart: 'Forgot password?' link under
  the Sign In button.

- supabase/002_device_tokens.sql (NEW): device_tokens table with
  unique (user_id, platform) constraint for clean upserts, RLS
  policies so users only see their own tokens, auto-touch
  updated_at trigger so the backend can prune stale tokens.
